<p><span class="script">template.gecko_minversion_header(1.9)</span></p>
<p>In Gecko 1.9, the findbar widget moved into toolkit, so it's available to any XUL application, as well as extensions.</p>
<p>For example, the standard findbar in Firefox 3.5 looks like this on the Mac:</p>
<p><img src="/@api/deki/files/3244/=findbar.png" style="width: 589px; height: 30px;" alt="findbar.png" class="internal default" /></p>
<p>You may attach a findbar to a particular browser element by either setting the findbar's <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("a-", "browserid")</span> attribute to the IDÂ of the browser element before the findbar element is bound, or by setting the findbar's <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("p-", "browser")</span> property to the browser element itself.</p>
<dl> <dt>Attributes</dt> <dd><span class="script">template.PrefAnch("a-", "browserid")</span>, <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("a-", "findnextaccesskey")</span>, <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("a-", "findpreviousaccesskey")</span>, <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("a-", "highlightaccesskey")</span>, <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("a-", "matchcaseaccesskey")</span></dd> <dt>Properties</dt> <dd><span class="script">template.PrefAnch("p-", "browser")</span>, <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("p-", "findMode")</span></dd> <dt>Methods</dt> <dd><span class="script">template.PrefAnch("m-", "close")</span>, <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("m-", "onFindAgainCommand")</span>, <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("m-", "open")</span>, <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("m-", "startFind")</span>, <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("m-", "toggleHighlight")</span></dd>
</dl>
<h3>Example</h3>
<pre>
&lt;browser type="content-primary" flex="1" id="content" src="about:blank"/&gt;
&lt;findbar id="FindToolbar" browserid="content"/&gt;
</pre>
